Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js App Router project

## Changes Made:

### 1. Installed Package
- Added @vercel/analytics (^2.0.0) to project dependencies
- Used npm to install the package (matching the project's .npmrc configuration)
- Created package-lock.json for dependency consistency

### 2. Updated Root Layout
Modified: app/layout.tsx
- Imported Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/next'
- Added proper <html> and <body> tags to the root layout (required for Next.js App Router)
- Placed <Analytics /> component inside the <body> tag, after the ClerkProvider and children
- Preserved existing ClerkProvider wrapper for API route authentication

### 3. Verified Implementation
- Successfully ran `npm run build` - build completed without errors
- All routes compiled successfully
- No TypeScript or linting errors introduced

## Implementation Details:

This is an App Router project (Next.js 15.3.6) with the following structure:
- Root layout at: app/layout.tsx
- Uses ClerkProvider for authentication
- Serves static HTML for the main UI via route handlers

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals when deployed to Vercel.

## Files Modified:
- app/layout.tsx - Added Analytics component import and integration
- package.json - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- package-lock.json - Created with locked dependency versions

The implementation follows Vercel's official documentation for App Router projects and maintains the existing code structure and patterns.
